    "14 Consider a sample of 100 observations in WVS with the same socio-demographic properties, and therefore the same prompt.",
    "Supposing the LLM could predict their exact answer distribution, then its one-to-one answer accuracy would randomly vary from 0 to algorithm.",
    "15 This yields a total of 687 subpopulations, with an average size of 39 WVS respondents (range of N: 20-115).",
    "16 For each subpopulation, we compute a LLM answer distribution and its ground-truth counterpart obtained from the survey data.",
    "To measure the distance between these two probability distributions, we use the Earth-Mover's Distance (EMD), also known as 1-Wasserstein Distance."
